Definition: acutely insightful and wise
Example: much too perspicacious to be taken in by such a spurious argument; observant and thoughtful, he was given to asking sagacious questions; a source of valuable insights and sapient advice to educators
Synonyms: noun, cognition, perspicaciousness, perspicacity, sagacious, sagaciousness, sapient, sapience, acutely, insightful, and, wise, much, too, to, be, taken, in, by, such, a, spurious, argument, observant, thoughtful, he, was, given, asking, questions, source, of, valuable, insights, advice, educators
Category: adj.all
